BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bloomberg-green-docs-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260814
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260815
SUMMARY:Deadline: Bloomberg Green Docs Competition 2026 (Short Climate Docu
 mentary)
DESCRIPTION:The Bloomberg Green Docs competition is open to all eligible fi
 lmmakers competing for a $25\,000 grand prize for a short climate document
 ary. The call seeks films that explore our climate future and reveal the w
 orld we are making today: ecosystems being restored\, tomorrow's zero-carb
 on communities being formed\, and habitat extremes warning of cascading cl
 imate consequences. REQUIREMENTS: films must address the urgency of climat
 e change and run under 10 minutes including credits. The jury awards a $25
 \,000 grand prize\, announced at the Bloomberg Green Docs Film Festival in
  New York City on 22 September 2026\, where the top five documentaries wil
 l be screened. Check the official rules on the competition site for eligib
 ility details. DEADLINE: submissions accepted through 14 August 2026.\n\nO
 rganisation: Bloomberg Green\nLocation: Open call for filmmakers (see elig
 ibility rules on the site)\; festival screening in New York City\, USA.\nA
 ward: $25\,000 grand prize awarded by a jury\; the top five documentaries 
 screen at the Bloomberg Green Docs Film Festival in New York City. No entr
 y fee stated.\nDuration: Winner announced at the festival on 22 September 
 2026\n\nMore: https://www.bloomberg.com/greendocs/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.bloomberg.com/greendocs/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open call for filmmakers (see eligibility rules on the site)\; fes
 tival screening in New York City\, USA.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:corridor-daisy-chain-commission-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260804
SUMMARY:Deadline: Corridor: DAISY CHAIN Artist Commission (Adur\, West Suss
 ex)
DESCRIPTION:Corridor seeks a socially-engaged artist based in the South Eas
 t of England working with moving image / lens-based media for DAISY CHAIN\
 , marking the 60th anniversary of Vera Chytilova's experimental film Daisi
 es (1966). The commissioned artist will work with a group of LGBTQIA+ youn
 g people aged 15-26 in Adur (West Sussex) to co-create new artworks: a 2-3
  minute moving image work and a series of 2D collage or mixed media artwor
 ks for public exhibition and screenings. DAISY CHAIN commissions six new a
 rtist moving image works overall (three England-based artists working with
  older women\, young women and LGBTQIA+ youth\; three artists in Czechia)\
 , developed in partnership with the National Film Museum in Prague (NaFilM
 ) and Brighton-based videoclub\, with results toured across England and Cz
 echia in 2027. EXPECTATIONS: devise about eight hands-on workshops incorpo
 rating film\, collage and mixed media (participants won't necessarily have
  an arts background)\; participate in 4-6 online peer sessions on collabor
 ative practice led by artist Annis Joslin\; complete exhibition-ready artw
 orks on time and to budget\; maintain a transparent dialogue on authorship
  with participants. Artists must have a participatory practice and experie
 nce of working creatively with young people. Note: to create a safe space\
 , workshops will not be publicly labelled as LGBTQIA+. FEE: GBP 4\,200 inc
 l. VAT plus travel and a materials budget. TIMELINE: shortlist notified 7 
 August\, online interviews 12 August 2026\; launch event in Adur/Worthing 
 March 2027. DEADLINE: 10am\, 3 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Corridor Proj
 ects\nLocation: Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-e
 ngaged artist based in the South East of England working with moving image
  / lens-based media.\nAward: GBP 4\,200 artist fee (inclusive of VAT) paid
  in instalments\, plus travel\, and an additional budget for materials for
  creative production\, workshops and exhibition outputs (e.g. print). No a
 pplication fee.\nDuration: September 2026 to July 2027: workshops Septembe
 r-January\, post-production to February 2027\, UK and Czech tour March-Jul
 y 2027\n\nMore: https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission?utm_source=a
 rtificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-engaged a
 rtist based in the South East of England working with moving image / lens-
 based media.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlinale-talents-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlinale Talents 2027 (Berlin International Film Festiva
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Berlinale Talents is the Berlin International Film Festival's t
 alent-development program: a week of workshops\, the Talents Lab and the T
 alent Project Market during the February 2027 Berlinale\, plus access to t
 he festival's industry network. ELIGIBILITY: international working film pr
 ofessionals with at least 1 feature\, 2 shorts\, or a widely screened or s
 treamed series\, across 15+ disciplines including directing\, sound design
 \, editing\, production\, cinematography and screenwriting. Participation 
 itself is free\; there is a EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early b
 ird before 19 August 2026) and travel and accommodation are not covered. D
 eadline 2 September 2026\, 12:00 CEST. Apply via the Berlinale Talents por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Berlinale / Berlin International Film Festival\nLoca
 tion: Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open inter
 nationally.\nAward: Free participation in the week-long professional progr
 am (Summit workshops\, Talents Lab\, Talent Project Market\, industry netw
 orking). NO stipend\; travel and accommodation are self-covered (national 
 film institutes often fund this\; Netherlands-based filmmakers can approac
 h the Netherlands Film Fund). EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early
  bird before 19 August 2026).\nDuration: One week during the Berlinale\, F
 ebruary 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open int
 ernationally.
END:VEVENT
