BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fondazione-prada-film-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260806
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260807
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fondazione Prada Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Fondazione Prada Film Fund is an annual EUR 1.5 million fun
 d backing 10 to 12 feature-length films (fiction\, documentary\, and anima
 tion\, 65 minutes or longer) across development\, production\, and post-pr
 oduction. ELIGIBILITY: independent producers and production companies with
  a track record (approximately two or more feature films premiered at majo
 r international festivals) and partial financing already secured\; this is
  aimed at established independent producers\, NOT individual emerging arti
 sts. DEADLINES: 6 August 2026 for projects in production\; 10 September 20
 26 for development and post-production projects (this card uses the earlie
 st deadline). Apply via the Fondazione Prada Film Fund page. NOTE: the fun
 der's primary page was not directly reachable at time of entry\; dates cor
 roborated via industry trade press (Screen\, Cineuropa). Verify the exact 
 track deadline before applying.\n\nOrganisation: Fondazione Prada\nLocatio
 n: Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers and 
 production companies.\nAward: EUR 1.5 million total pool supporting 10 to 
 12 feature films. Development grants EUR 15\,000 to 80\,000\; production g
 rants EUR 30\,000 to 250\,000\; post-production grants EUR 40\,000 to 100\
 ,000. No application fee.\nDuration: Feature film funding (development\, p
 roduction\, or post-production)\n\nMore: https://www.fondazioneprada.org/f
 ilm-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://www.fondazioneprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers
  and production companies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:guardian-arte-democracy-at-stake-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Democracy at Stake in Europe: Short Documentary Fund
DESCRIPTION:Guardian Documentaries and arte.tv have opened a short document
 ary film fund on the theme 'Democracy at Stake in Europe'\, supporting the
  development and production of a character-led documentary short exploring
  threats\, pressures and challenges facing democratic societies across Eur
 ope. The aim is to amplify personal stories that help audiences understand
  democracy in Europe today and to stimulate public debate\; suggested area
 s of focus include press freedom\, civic trust and democratic participatio
 n. AWARD: one project receives GBP 10\,000 in production support\; alongsi
 de the financial award\, the selected filmmaker receives editorial and cre
 ative input from the partners\, with distribution through Guardian and art
 e.tv platforms. The funding can be used for work linked to the film's deve
 lopment and production\, such as research\, filming and post-production\, 
 subject to the applicant's proposed budget and plan. ELIGIBILITY: open to 
 European filmmakers aged 18 or over\; the call is focused on a single shor
 t documentary and is intended for projects where individual experience and
  perspective are central to telling a wider story about democratic life in
  Europe. Deadline 14 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Guardian Documentari
 es and arte.tv\nLocation: Europe.\nAward: GBP 10\,000 in production suppor
 t for one short documentary project\, plus editorial and creative input fr
 om the partners and distribution through Guardian and arte.tv platforms.\n
 Duration: Development and production of a single short documentary.\n\nMor
 e: https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-expanded-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Expanded Orbit 1st Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Expanded Orbit is the first edition of an international 
 training programme dedicated to immersive storytelling and XR-based practi
 ces\, run by the CIRCLE Training Initiative in partnership with Onassis ON
 X. It supports women and gender-expansive filmmakers\, artists\, XR creato
 rs\, and multidisciplinary storytellers working across XR\, MR\, VR\, AR\,
  AI\, and game-based narratives\, with no prior XR experience required. Se
 lected individuals or teams of up to two receive individual mentorship\, g
 roup sessions\, co-creation workshops\, and structured feedback\, plus acc
 ess to an international network of professionals. The in-person training t
 akes place from November 21 to 26\, 2026\, in Athens\, Greece. Applicants 
 should be developing a project with a strong artistic vision and clear int
 erest in immersive formats\, ideally with a producer attached and partial 
 budget secured. A participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per person applies\, wit
 h scholarships of up to 50 percent available based on financial need.\n\nO
 rganisation: CIRCLE Training Initiative (with Onassis ONX)\nLocation: Athe
 ns\, Greece\nAward: No cash stipend. Provides individual mentorship from w
 orld-leading experts\, group sessions\, co-creation workshops\, structured
  feedback\, and access to an international professional network across fil
 m\, art\, design\, and technology. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per per
 son (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\, with scholarships covering up to 50 per
 cent available for those with financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee
  per person (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\; up to 50 percent scholarships a
 vailable\nDuration: 6 days (in-person training)\n\nMore: https://www.docci
 rcle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-fiction-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Fiction Orbit 3rd Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Fiction Orbit is a one-week retreat in Herceg Novi\, Mon
 tenegro for up to six fiction feature film projects led by teams of women 
 and gender-expansive filmmakers developing their second\, third\, or fourt
 h narrative feature. Participants work with leading experts on script deve
 lopment\, legal and production strategy\, career positioning\, and receive
  psychological support throughout the creative process. Applicants must id
 entify as a woman or gender-expansive filmmaker\, work as a screenwriter\,
  director\, or producer\, have completed at least one feature\, and submit
  a project with a producer attached. Accommodation and meals are provided\
 , but travel is not covered\, and a participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per pe
 rson applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship is available annually fo
 r those with demonstrated financial need. The third edition runs October 2
 5 to November 1\, 2026\, with applications due July 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: CIRCLE Training Initiative\nLocation: Herceg Novi\, Montenegro\nAwar
 d: Accommodation and meals provided\; in-depth script consultations\, lega
 l and production strategy guidance\, career development mentorship\, and p
 sychological support. Travel not covered. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 
 per person applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship available annually
  for participants from lower-income countries\, those without national fun
 ding\, or with demonstrated financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee (
 accommodation and meals included\; travel not covered)\; 50 percent schola
 rship available for demonstrated need\nDuration: One week\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Herceg Novi\, Montenegro
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:insideout-refocus-fund-postproduction-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260722
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260723
SUMMARY:Deadline: Inside Out RE:Focus Fund Post-Production Grants 2026
DESCRIPTION:Established in 2018 through a lead gift from Martha McCain\, In
 side Out's RE:Focus Fund addresses industry inequities by providing direct
  financial support to women\, non-binary\, and/or trans filmmakers telling
  2SLGBTQ+ stories. Launched in 2019\, the RE:Focus Fund Post-Production Gr
 ants support the post-production and promotion of short and feature films.
  Applications for the 2026 round open 29 June 2026. ELIGIBILITY: women\, n
 on-binary\, and/or trans filmmakers whose projects tell 2SLGBTQ+ stories\;
  per the FAQ\, international projects may be eligible to apply. The reques
 ted funding amount is determined by the applicant\, and unsuccessful appli
 cants can request feedback and reapply the following year. Inside Out also
  runs other RE:Focus initiatives\, including a new Residency program for f
 irst-time feature filmmakers facing intersectional barriers. KEY DATES: su
 bmissions open 29 June 2026\, close 22 July 2026\, with notifications by 1
 5 August 2026. Apply and read the FAQ via the Eventival page linked from t
 he RE:Focus Fund site\; questions to industry@insideout.ca.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: Inside Out (Toronto 2SLGBTQ+ Film Festival)\nLocation: Toronto\, Canada
  (Inside Out is a Canadian organisation\; international projects may apply
 \, see FAQ)\nAward: Post-production grant funding to support the completio
 n and promotion of short and feature films\; the requested amount is set b
 y the applicant (see the FAQ 'How much funding can I request?'). Since 201
 8 the RE:Focus Fund has distributed more than CAD 300\,000 in grants and p
 rograms. No application fee.\nDuration: One-off post-production grant\n\nM
 ore: https://insideout.ca/initiatives/re-focus-fund/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://insideout.ca/initiatives/re-focus-fund/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Toronto\, Canada (Inside Out is a Canadian organisation\; internat
 ional projects may apply\, see FAQ)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:100-voices-of-florida-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260920
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260921
SUMMARY:Deadline: 100 Voices of Florida Film Grant
DESCRIPTION:100 Voices of Florida is a grant for filmmakers and screenwrite
 rs that awards up to USD 5\,000 in unrestricted funds\, which winners can 
 use for finishing funds\, festival submission fees\, cast and crew reimbur
 sements\, production\, or anything else. Applicants submit either a short 
 film (under twenty minutes) or a script (twenty pages or less)\; films in 
 other languages must include accurate English subtitles\, and scripts must
  be in English. The grant is open to writers\, directors\, and producers w
 ho are at least 18 years old\, and creative teams may submit\, though only
  one entrant receives the award. A panel of judges with professional filmm
 aking experience evaluates entries\, and the winner also receives a meetin
 g with an industry professional. The deadline for the current cycle is Sep
 tember 20\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation: 100 Voices of Florida\nLocation: Florid
 a\, United States\nAward: Up to USD 5\,000 (unrestricted) USD 25 applicati
 on fee with a Florida connection\, USD 35 without\nDuration: One-time gran
 t\n\nMore: https://www.100vof.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.100vof.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_mediu
 m=referral
LOCATION:Florida\, United States
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:genera-short-film-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Genera Short Film Fund 2026 (current round)
DESCRIPTION:Genera Films offers up to GBP 5\,000 in funding for a short fil
 m project\, regardless of genre. Applications are welcome at any stage of 
 a project's evolution: initial development\, production\, post-production\
 , or preparing for the festival circuit. Applicants can either be Pro Memb
 ers or pay a one-off funding fee that ranges from GBP 40 to GBP 50 (Earlyb
 ird GBP 40\, Regular GBP 45\, Final GBP 50)\; Pro Membership offers additi
 onal benefits described on the Membership tab. Established in 2017\, Gener
 a Films champions short filmmakers worldwide\, drawing talent from over 17
 6 countries and having supported over 50 projects as an independent patron
 . CURRENT ROUND TIMELINE: round opens 2 January\; Earlybird deadline 28 Fe
 bruary (GBP 40)\; Regular deadline 30 April (GBP 45)\; Final deadline 30 J
 une (GBP 50)\; shortlist announced 10 July\; funded films announced 17 Jul
 y.\n\nOrganisation: Genera Films\nLocation: Global\; open to short filmmak
 ers worldwide (talent drawn from over 176 countries).\nAward: Up to GBP 5\
 ,000 in funding for a short film project\, any genre. Application requires
  either Pro Membership or a one-off funding fee (GBP 40 to GBP 50 dependin
 g on deadline tier).\nDuration: Apply at any project stage: development\, 
 production\, post-production\, or festival circuit.\n\nMore: https://gener
 afilms.com/powered-by/genera?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://generafilms.com/powered-by/genera?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Global\; open to short filmmakers worldwide (talent drawn from ove
 r 176 countries).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fluxus-experimental-film-festival-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fluxus Experimental Film & Media Arts Festival 2026: Call
  for Submissions
DESCRIPTION:Fluxus is a contemporary short film and media arts festival hos
 ted in partnership between Factory Media Centre\, Hamilton Artists Inc and
  McMaster University School of the Arts. Its mission is to provide an acce
 ssible forum for the exhibition of creative\, experimental\, moving-image 
 art forms\, and to develop connections between Canadian media artists\, ar
 ts institutions and the public. Fluxus showcases experimental and boundary
 -pushing media works from artists of all levels working in Canada\; submis
 sions are free and unrestricted by theme\, open to a spectrum of artforms 
 including but not limited to animation\, documentary\, video art\, collage
  film\, music video and experimental film. The festival takes place over t
 wo screenings at Hamilton Artists Inc on Friday 18 and Saturday 19 Septemb
 er 2026 (the Friday screening is dedicated to emerging media artists and f
 ilmmakers)\; all screenings are free to attend. REMUNERATION: there is no 
 submission fee\, and IMAA-scale artist remuneration is paid to successful 
 applicants within 30 days of the screenings. GUIDELINES: artists must be c
 urrently based and/or working in Canada\; work must be short format (15 mi
 nutes or less) and no more than 5 years old (2021 or later)\; submissions 
 are digital Vimeo or YouTube links (private/password-protected accepted if
  the password is provided)\; solo artists\, groups\, collectives and colla
 borative works are welcome\, with a limit of one submission per artist/gro
 up/collective\; films must be independent projects over which the artist r
 etains full creative and artistic control. AI POLICY: Fluxus discourages t
 he use of generative AI in submitted works\; if AI factors into the creati
 ve process\, its use must be declared and described (see Factory Media Cen
 tre's Policy on the Use of Generative AI). APPLY via the online submission
  form with an artist bio (75 words max)\, artist CV (PDF\, 3 pages max)\, 
 a brief description of the work (100 words max)\, entry information\, the 
 video link\, and two image stills. Notification is expected in August\; du
 e to the high quantity of submissions\, only selected artists will be cont
 acted. Fluxus is committed to equity and strongly encourages applications 
 from Black and Indigenous artists\, persons with disabilities\, ethnic or 
 racial minorities\, immigrants and refugees\, Francophones\, LGBTQI+ perso
 ns\, women\, and persons of all socio-economic backgrounds. Deadline: Wedn
 esday 15 July 2026 at 11:59pm EST. Questions: programming@theinc.ca.\n\nOr
 ganisation: Hamilton Artists Inc.\, in partnership with McMaster Universit
 y School of the Arts and Factory Media Centre\nLocation: Hamilton\, Ontari
 o\, Canada\; submitting artists must be currently based and/or working in 
 Canada.\nAward: Free to submit (NO entry fee). IMAA-scale artist remunerat
 ion (a screening/exhibition fee following the Independent Media Arts Allia
 nce fee schedule) is paid to successful applicants within 30 days of the s
 creenings.\nDuration: Two screenings\, 18 and 19 September 2026\n\nMore: h
 ttps://www.theinc.ca/fluxus-call-submissions?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.theinc.ca/fluxus-call-submissions?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hamilton\, Ontario\, Canada\; submitting artists must be currently
  based and/or working in Canada.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:casa-pip-residency-filmmakers-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: CASA PIP Residency for Filmmakers
DESCRIPTION:CASA PIP is a residency program in Portugal founded and run by 
 filmmakers. It encourages residents to slow down and play\, providing film
 makers with the time\, peace\, space\, and general "rulelessness" to move 
 meaningfully forward on their work\, whether it is a whole project or just
  the budding idea for one. The residency is free to attend. ELIGIBILITY: o
 pen internationally to filmmakers. There is a EUR 35 application fee. Dead
 line: July 31\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation: CASA PIP\nLocation: Portugal\; open
  internationally to filmmakers.\nAward: Free residency (no cost to attend)
 \, offering time\, space\, and peace to work on a project or an early idea
 . A EUR 35 application fee applies.\nDuration: Residency\n\nMore: https://
 casapip.com/apply?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://casapip.com/apply?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
LOCATION:Portugal\; open internationally to filmmakers.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:inevitable-accelerate-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260716T125850Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Deadline: Inevitable Foundation: Accelerate Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Accelerate Fellowship is a four-month rewriting sprint that
  gives disabled film and television writers USD 30\,000 in unrestricted fu
 nding and bespoke mentorship to develop a spec script to market. Through w
 riters groups\, one-on-one mentorship\, guidance from Inevitable Foundatio
 n staff\, and access to leading film and television writers\, the program 
 offers everything a disabled writer needs to get a script ready to take to
  market\; this year's program also encourages nuanced disability represent
 ation in the projects themselves. Benefits include a USD 30\,000 unrestric
 ted grant to cover living expenses so Fellows can focus full-time on writi
 ng\, frequent conversations and workshops with leading writers and showrun
 ners\, ongoing mentorship and check-ins with the Inevitable team\, and a c
 ommunity of disabled screenwriting peers. The Fellowship is supported by N
 etflix. Fellows retain all rights to their work. ELIGIBILITY: self-identif
 ies as disabled (physical\, intellectual\, developmental\, visible or invi
 sible disabilities\, and mental health conditions)\; 18 or older\; current
 ly pursuing a career in writing for film or television\; not enrolled in a
 n accredited degree program\; and currently or previously worked in the en
 tertainment industry. Applicants must also meet at least one of: has an ag
 ent or manager\; member of the WGA\, Animation Guild\, or equivalent union
 \; has sold a script\, TV show\, or pitch\; has staffed on a TV show or re
 ceived a movie writing credit\; has been or is in development with a major
  production company\, studio\, or network\; has placed in a prominent scre
 enwriting competition\; or has participated in a screenwriting or filmmaki
 ng lab\, program\, or residency. Writing teams may apply\, but only disabl
 ed members receive the unrestricted funding (and if both members are disab
 led they apply as a team and split the grant). International applicants ar
 e accepted but must be available within the US Pacific Time working day an
 d are subject to additional review under U.S. Treasury regulations. Former
  Accelerate Fellows are not eligible. The script need not be finished\, an
 d projects from any genre are welcome (the market currently favors comedy\
 , horror\, thriller\, rom-com\, and young adult). APPLICATION: a single ro
 und open 28 May 2026 through 17 June 2026\; first complete the Program Eli
 gibility Questionnaire\, then if eligible submit information about yoursel
 f and your career\, a writing sample with title and logline\, details on t
 he intended project\, and short-answer questions on your goals. TIMELINE: 
 applications open May 2026\; semi-finalist interviews July to August 2026\
 ; Fellows selected August 2026\; Fellowship runs September to December 202
 6. Selections are made by Inevitable Foundation staff. Questions: programs
 @inevitable.foundation.\n\nOrganisation: Inevitable Foundation\nLocation: 
 Remote (US-based program\; Fellows must be available for meetings within t
 he US Pacific Time working day). Open to applicants outside the US subject
  to additional review\nAward: USD 30\,000 unrestricted grant to cover livi
 ng expenses\, plus bespoke mentorship\, writers groups\, workshops\, and o
 ff-the-record conversations with leading writers and showrunners. No appli
 cation fee.\nDuration: 4 months\, September to December 2026\n\nMore: http
 s://inevitable.foundation/accelerate?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk
 &utm_medium=referral
URL:https://inevitable.foundation/accelerate?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote (US-based program\; Fellows must be available for meetings 
 within the US Pacific Time working day). Open to applicants outside the US
  subject to additional review
END:VEVENT
